      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if originalism is about restraint, how do people explain the way it's used to strike down modern rights that the founders definitely didn't think about, like privacy or marriage equality? is it actually a legal theory or just a way to revert to an older social order?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
